                            <comment id="14139960" author="hiranya" created="Fri, 19 Sep 2014 04:19:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nuwan, any more info on this. An error log or something?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14142203" author="hiranya" created="Sat, 20 Sep 2014 21:13:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This turned out to be more serious than previously expected. Looking into this now. I think I know what the problem is.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14142213" author="hiranya" created="Sat, 20 Sep 2014 22:12:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed and added a test case (integration test 10003). Fix was to call setSerializationCompleteWithoutData method for all outgoing requests that don&apos;t have an entity body. Requests like OPTIONS and HEAD fall under this category in HTTP Core, so calling the above method triggers the necessary I/O operations at the TargetHandler.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14142694" author="hudson" created="Sun, 21 Sep 2014 20:50:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;SUCCESS: Integrated in Synapse - Trunk #4900 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Synapse%20-%20Trunk/4900/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Synapse%20-%20Trunk/4900/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
